a) a user interface for submitting applications for community tax certificates or permits/clearances;
b) credential issuers responsible for issuing verifiable credentials based on eligibility criteria;
c) verifiers responsible for verifying verifiable credentials using machine learning algorithms;
d) payment gateways responsible for processing cryptocurrency payments from applicants;
e) a blockchain ledger for storing transaction data.

3. A method of processing cryptocurrency payments using payment gateways in conjunction with a blockchain ledger for storing transaction data in a system for issuing community tax certificates or permits/clearances as digital certificates using verifiable credentials.

